{"key":"post-11981643","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>11981643</id>\n<content>All you need is the PVC pipe and a bunch of fittings, a hack saw to cut it and some PVC cement to glue it together.&amp;nbsp; What you'll need to do is measure your available space, and then just go to the hardware store and meditate on the fittings you see on the shelf.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Don't be embarrassed to pick up the fittings and hold them in the position you imagine gluing them later.&amp;nbsp; The store clerk can't help you, so just tell him/her you're trying to figure out what you need, and you just need time to look at what's there and figure out your plan.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you're like me, you'll probably come home with not enough to finish the job, and have to go back for the rest of what you forgot the first time.&amp;nbsp;  Once you wrap the plastic around your frame, tie it in place with bailing wire or electrical twist ties.&amp;nbsp; You'll have to punch holes in the plastic to tie it to the frame.&amp;nbsp; I use a nail or my knife.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>11981772</next>\n<prev>11981452</prev>\n<first>11981452</first>\n<last>11981772</last>\n<when>1265572229</when>\n<utime>02/07/10 09:50 PM</utime>\n</post>"}